Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yu
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1051 "Intrigue \Nat Morikawa Mansion (Part Two)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.31,0:00:04.73,DCItalic,YUZABURO,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, an ice cream cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:07.08,DCItalic,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better eat it quick before it melts.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.08,0:00:08.73,DCItalic,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.23,0:00:11.91,DCItalic,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro, would you cut the cake for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.91,0:00:12.74,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.10,0:00:20.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We were invited to the remote \Nisland where the mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.21,0:00:24.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,of Morikawa Holdings chairman \NMorikawa Yuzan is located
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.42,0:00:27.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to advise him on the rewriting of his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:33.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}At the mansion were Yuzan and his heirs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:32.05,Yuzan,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Morikawa Yuzan (68) \NMorikawa Group Chairman
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.27,0:00:36.55,Yuichiro,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Morikawa Yuichiro (33) \NSelf-employed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:36.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}his eldest son Morikawa Yuichiro-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.77,0:00:39.43,Yujiro,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Morikawa Yujiro (31) \NMorikawa Holdings Executive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.01,0:00:39.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}his second son Morikawa Yujiro-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.43,0:00:42.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and his third son Morikawa Yuzaburo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:42.10,Yuzaburo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Morikawa Yuzaburo (27) \NMorikawa Livestock Rancher
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.38,0:00:46.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Also present were Yuzan's \Nlawyer Oi Hiroki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.06,0:00:45.77,Oi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Oi Hiroki (36) \NLawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:49.19,Yuka,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Shito Yuka (24) \NChief Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.18,0:00:48.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and chief butler Shito Yuka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:55.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next day, the third son Yuzaburo-san \Nwas found murdered in a locked room,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.32,0:01:00.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and even Yujiro-san turned up dead, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.68,0:01:05.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious clouds block your field of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.53,0:01:07.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Clear them away with deductive \Nreasoning and the sky sparkles!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.34,0:01:09.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An inheritance dispute swirls about the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:11.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is the mystery of the locked \Nroom and the family's motives?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:13.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:14.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.76,0:01:17.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:05.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}Intrigue at Morikawa Mansion \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.68,0:03:02.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Intrigue at Morikawa Mansion, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.81,0:03:08.72,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yujiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:10.63,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.85,0:03:13.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.19,0:03:17.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is definitely a serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.56,0:03:19.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oi-san, you still won't change your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:22.86,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzan's mind has not changed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.86,0:03:27.81,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,is what I'd like to say, but I \Nalready called the police yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:29.70,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.70,0:03:34.54,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,The police should arrive by the time \Nthe will is rewritten this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:37.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:42.86,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be getting started on \Nthe investigation, like that boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.48,0:03:47.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bruise on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.48,0:03:49.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This must've killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.58,0:03:53.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:03:56.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.81,0:04:02.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, what do you suppose \Nthis dark stain is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.27,0:04:07.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's... not mud. It's coal-colored.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:08.51,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:11.34,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you supposed to be a great detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.34,0:04:14.14,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and catch the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:15.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:18.32,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,My brothers were killed one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:20.94,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how you look \Nat it, I'm clearly next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:23.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:26.82,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,My father's heirs have \Nbeen killed in succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:28.30,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.30,0:04:31.20,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What good will it do to take out \Nyour frustrations on the detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:34.84,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:37.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.20,0:04:41.32,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to my room. I have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:55.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this inheritance dispute \Nturned into a serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.95,0:04:59.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister. Have you already \Nfigured out who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.91,0:05:01.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.24,0:05:03.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:05.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.67,0:05:09.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Normally you'd assume it's \Nthe eldest son Yuichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.67,0:05:14.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But it's hard to believe he did \Nit based on his earlier behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.95,0:05:20.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But it goes without saying that he stands \Nto benefit the most from their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:28.39,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.87,0:05:32.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that \Nlawyer is suspicious, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:33.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't want us to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.02,0:05:35.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.58,0:05:39.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how you look at it, it seems \Nlike he's afraid of the murders coming to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.98,0:05:49.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Or what if it's actually Yuka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:50.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:51.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.73,0:05:54.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They say every rose has its thorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.94,0:05:58.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's your reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:06.77,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Flavor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:11.16,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,texture, and taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.16,0:06:12.30,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.97,0:06:16.36,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the soft serve I've been looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.82,0:06:22.19,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Its jet black appearance doesn't give the \Nslightest hint of its mild chocolate sweetness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:26.40,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,The high-quality cacao flavor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:29.53,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,spreads throughout the mouth and \Nleaves a refreshing aftertaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.81,0:06:31.83,DCMain,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's truly perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.60,0:06:39.39,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yujiro and Yuzaburo are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.39,0:06:41.87,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,The inheritance is all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.87,0:06:43.94,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Now I just need my father to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:47.99,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Once he's dead, it'll be my time to shine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.33,0:06:51.80,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I shall reign supreme!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.32,0:07:03.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.30,0:07:04.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I-I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.12,0:07:11.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:15.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,One shot through the heart from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.28,0:07:19.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably didn't even \Nhave time to feel pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:20.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.38,0:07:22.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look. His tongue is black.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:24.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:26.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:28.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.97,0:07:34.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.88,0:07:35.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.14,0:07:37.19,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:40.10,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They say every rose has its thorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:41.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it really be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.77,0:07:45.86,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, I heard a gunshot. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.08,0:07:50.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san was shot. Yuka-san, \Nstay with the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.08,0:07:52.36,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.17,0:07:59.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you follow me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.89,0:08:02.65,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave you by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.65,0:08:06.08,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I manage everything at this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:09.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's in the room up ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:13.09,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,It should be a tool room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:16.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:21.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka-san, what's the story with this rifle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:26.82,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The master bought it a few years ago \Nwhen some boars tore up the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:30.41,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The lock's been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:40.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.67,0:08:51.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.65,0:08:52.42,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:55.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you show me Yuichiro-san's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:09:00.09,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.09,0:09:00.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:05.68,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought one of the three \Nbrothers was the culprit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:08.06,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,but they're all dead now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.61,0:09:11.94,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Who could the culprit be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:19.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Oi-san, we weren't \Nable to confirm your alibi either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:22.74,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,You think I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.74,0:09:24.45,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.45,0:09:26.73,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a simple lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:30.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure even a lawyer \Nis capable of killing a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:35.63,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I believe detectives \Nare capable of murder as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.63,0:09:45.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:50.69,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san had been working on \Nresearching a new flavor for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.96,0:09:55.12,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The things on that table are \Nprobably research materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:07.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:09.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,black soft serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.27,0:10:10.75,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.77,0:10:14.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:15.92,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.92,0:10:18.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you love most in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:20.83,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, that would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.22,0:10:39.07,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, kid. What is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.06,0:10:43.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out who killed Yuichiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.97,0:10:46.59,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? How interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:49.04,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.44,0:10:53.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san was killed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.25,0:10:55.61,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Killed by?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.42,0:11:07.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san was killed by...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.20,0:11:09.63,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Killed by?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:12.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Morikawa Yuzan-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:14.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.45,0:11:20.33,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,You must be rather certain to \Naccuse me of being the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:21.95,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.95,0:11:23.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But first...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.19,0:11:28.10,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.10,0:11:36.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been using this to watch everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:40.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your dead sons and us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:45.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The murders that have been \Nhappening since yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.40,0:11:51.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,were a series of unfortunate events \Ncaused by your tremendous legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.10,0:11:56.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.49,0:11:59.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,First, there's Yuzaburo-san's \Nlocked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.86,0:12:03.53,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You figured out the mystery \Nof that locked room murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.34,0:12:05.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.13,0:12:10.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,At first I couldn't believe it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.53,0:12:13.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but I became certain after hearing \Nwhat Yuka-san had to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.56,0:12:18.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san created that locked room \Nusing the special soft serve machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.80,0:12:22.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Before the locked room was created,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.13,0:12:26.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro-san and Yuzaburo-san \Nwere probably chatting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.38,0:12:29.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,in Yuzaburo-san's room over drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:35.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,During their conversation, Yuichiro-san \Nsaid he'd have some soft serve
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.36,0:12:40.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and used the special soft serve \Nmachine installed in the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.33,0:12:44.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The machine's temperature \Ncan be set as low as -50°,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:51.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the valve's temperature can be set \Nas high as 40°, all of it on a timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:57.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Undetected by Yuzaburo-san, Yuichiro-san \Ndirected the cooling system's vent
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:13:00.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,outwards and set the \Nmachine to cool the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:04.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He cleaned up his own glass and left the \Nroom with a cone of soft serve in hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:08.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,leaving the passed out drunk \NYuzaburo-san alone in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:11.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once Yuichiro-san was outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.42,0:13:14.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he inserted the soft serve into the keyhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:18.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Before the soft serve could melt away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.49,0:13:24.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the machine cooled the entire room at -50°.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.56,0:13:29.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the time Yuzaburo-san noticed something \Nwas wrong and attempted to exit the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:32.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the soft serve in the keyhole had frozen,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:35.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,making it impossible to leave the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:40.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Yuzaburo-san froze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:42.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a trick using
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.70,0:13:46.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,special soft serve machines that could \Nonly be pulled off at this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:52.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After Yuzaburo-san froze to death, \Nthe timer was set to heat the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.29,0:13:58.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The frozen room itself and soft serve in the \Nkeyhole thawed, creating the locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.76,0:14:01.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yujiro-san was murdered when
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:08.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yujiro-san asked to meet Yuichiro-san \Nin front of the soft serve tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:11.70,Yu,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,460)}Yu
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:14.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was a note written by Yujiro-san \Nin the trash can of Yuichiro-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.25,0:14:14.95,Note,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(460,1)}Meet me in front of the tanks at 4PM today \NYu
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.24,0:14:18.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It probably happened after \Ntheir conversation turned sour
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.30,0:14:20.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and they got into an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.93,0:14:24.92,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was Yujiro who was \Ntrying to kill Yuichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:25.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:32.25,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,After arguing over their \Nshares of the inheritance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.25,0:14:35.16,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,a fight broke out, and then this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.28,0:14:43.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.75,0:14:47.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then Yuichiro-san hid the \Nbody inside the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:50.14,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your deduction was perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:53.90,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,but what made you certain he did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.78,0:14:56.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:14:57.84,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.36,0:15:02.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Materials for the black soft \Nserve Yuichiro-san developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:05.72,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's practically jet black.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:07.51,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's bamboo charcoal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:08.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.77,0:15:13.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Jet black chocolate soft serve \Nmade with bamboo charcoal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.13,0:15:17.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the project Yuichiro-san \Nhad been working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:23.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Pieces of bamboo charcoal were \Nleft at both crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:27.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,At one scene, the pieces of charcoal \Nwere stuck to the soft serve machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:31.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and at the other, there was a charcoal \Nstain on the floor of the tank room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:36.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And Yuichiro-san's tongue \Nwas black when he was shot
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:40.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,because of this soft serve \Nmade with bamboo charcoal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.80,0:15:43.29,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you call hard evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.64,0:15:48.28,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,So why do you think I killed Yuichiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.28,0:15:50.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:52.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.49,0:15:55.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's terribly complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.66,0:15:58.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.69,0:16:03.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,like who knew how to use a hunting gun
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:05.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,or where it was stored in this mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.19,0:16:07.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but it was something simple that clued me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:09.69,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,And what was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.53,0:16:13.97,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:15.70,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this that famous phenomenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.00,0:16:17.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:21.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After I heard the gunshot and visited \Nthe yard where Yuichiro-san fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:24.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the room I believed \Nthe shot came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:29.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that room with the rifle, \NI noticed something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.12,0:16:33.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was the smell of \Ngunpowder left by the gunshot
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.00,0:16:34.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the smell of the medicines \Nkept in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.69,0:16:36.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:40.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was your smell, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.69,0:16:42.25,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,My smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.25,0:16:46.40,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean my old man smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.14,0:16:53.84,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.41,0:17:01.26,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,By using my last bit of strength \Nto kill him, I dug my own grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.56,0:17:04.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you kill your own son?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:07.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you have let the police handle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.98,0:17:12.76,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was blinded by money and \Nkilled his own brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:16.04,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't trouble someone \Nelse with dealing with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.58,0:17:20.18,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,As his father, I took \Nresponsibility for what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.48,0:17:25.57,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,I originally plotted to \Nreturn them to their senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.57,0:17:26.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Return them to their senses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:31.82,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,I taught my sons to share \Nsince they were boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.12,0:17:35.24,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,I told them I was planning to rewrite my will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.24,0:17:41.83,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,to have one heir so they'd remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:45.93,DCItalic,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the willingness to \Nshare with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.93,0:17:47.96,DCItalic,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.96,0:17:49.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they didn't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:51.11,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:54.80,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, they started \Nkilling each other instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.32,0:17:57.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Yuzaburo-san tried \Nto kill someone, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:17:58.97,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:18:02.48,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was trying to kill Yuichiro, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.48,0:18:07.33,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro probably figured \Nit out and killed him first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:12.57,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,After all my hard work,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.47,0:18:18.45,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've lost everything on my deathbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:22.08,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:26.83,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,The more money I made, the \Nunhappier my family became.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.53,0:18:32.34,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,They used to be so close, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:36.75,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I want you to do something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.83,0:18:41.18,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the police what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:43.22,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.11,0:18:51.00,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you make sure Yuichiro's \Nrecipe sees the light of day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.00,0:18:51.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:55.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That soft serve looked tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:56.96,DCMain,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:18.13,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Edogawa Conan-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.58,0:19:23.82,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I was instructed by the late Morikawa Yuzan
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.82,0:19:27.52,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,to entrust you with the \Ndistribution of his legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:28.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.45,0:19:30.13,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.57,0:19:34.02,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,He said to leave everything up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.97,0:19:35.77,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:38.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But wasn't Kogoro-no-ojisan hired to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.55,0:19:41.32,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Once the murders happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.32,0:19:45.90,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Morikawa Yuzan said he'd entrust the \Nmatter to whoever solved the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.33,0:19:56.34,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Who, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.54,0:19:57.38,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.38,0:20:03.18,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I've been told to leave the entire \Nmatter of the inheritance up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:08.60,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.88,0:20:11.35,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,As you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:14.23,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:19.61,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,This it the recipe for bamboo charcoal \Nsoft serve Yuichiro left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.14,0:20:24.06,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,I've also received instructions \Nto make it public.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:28.62,DCItalic,YUZABURO,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, an ice cream cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:31.77,DCItalic,YUZAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yuichiro, would you cut the cake for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.77,0:20:32.62,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.36,0:20:38.63,DCItalic,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Four pieces?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.04,0:20:41.21,DCItalic,YUZABURO,0000,0000,0000,,But there's only three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:42.63,DCItalic,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Is one piece for Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:44.63,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.27,0:20:48.14,DCItalic,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.53,0:20:54.49,DCItalic,YUJIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Yuka-chan, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.49,0:20:56.40,DCItalic,YUZABURO,0000,0000,0000,,Have some ice cream cake with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:20:58.65,DCItalic,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.06,0:21:00.90,DCItalic,YUICHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better hurry, or it'll melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.14,0:21:11.41,DCMain,YUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.90,0:21:14.41,DCMain,OI,0000,0000,0000,,Good choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.71,0:22:51.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The case was solved while I was asleep again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.68,0:22:56.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, is that young lady really \Ntaking over the entire Morikawa Group?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.17,0:23:02.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? Shouldn't someone who loves \Nsoft serve inherit his legacy anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.51,0:23:05.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuka-san.
